trend_summary: From earliest to latest dates, built surface expanded moderately, mainly around existing settlements. A large housing subdivision emerged on the north-east ridge, while the southern town thickened and spread westward. Forest cover shrank as fields and roads widened, especially near the lake. Overall built-up footprint rose but landscape remains predominantly green, marking a sparsely built suburban zone.
notable_changes: New residential estate constructed on the north-east plateau, replacing forest cover.
Progressive infill and edge expansion of the southern township, increasing roof density.
Clearing of forest southwest of the central lake, converted to mixed cropland.
Extension and paving of road corridors linking northern and eastern neighbourhoods.
